# Cursor AI Rules for mnemonic.fyi

## Project Context
This is mnemonic.fyi - an AI-powered knowledge search application that searches across Slack and Notion.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 with App Router
- OpenAI GPT-4 and embeddings
- Supabase database with vector search
- Slack and Notion API integrations
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Deployed on Vercel

## Key Files
- `src/app/page.tsx` - Main landing page with demo toggle
- `src/components/SearchInterface.tsx` - Search functionality
- `src/components/AdminPanel.tsx` - Data ingestion panel
- `src/lib/search.ts` - Core search logic with vector similarity
- `src/lib/slack.ts` - Slack API integration
- `src/lib/notion.ts` - Notion API integration

## Current Issues
- Slack API missing scopes (channels:read, users:read, chat:read)
- Vercel deployment needs to be set up
- Domain mnemonics-red.vercel.app not working

## Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run lint` - Lint code

## Environment Variables
All API keys are in .env.local (OpenAI, Supabase, Slack, Notion)

## When helping with this project:
1. Always check the current state of files before making changes
2. Test changes locally with `npm run dev`
3. Commit changes to Git when working
4. Focus on fixing deployment and Slack integration issues
